    "Short Hypothesis": "We hypothesize that spectral curvature-aware precision routing can significantly improve the accuracy and efficiency of machine learning models by adaptively allocating precision and optimizing geometric subspace diagnostics.",
    "Related Work": "Existing works on precision routing and geometric subspace diagnostics have shown promising results, but they often rely on heuristic approaches and lack rigorous mathematical accounting. Our proposal differs from existing works by integrating spectral quantization theory with curvature-aware precision routing, providing a more theoretically grounded and efficient approach.",
