The proposal includes a clear hypothesis, related work, abstract, experiments, and risk factors, providing a comprehensive overview of the research idea. 

The experiments will evaluate the effectiveness of the spectral curvature-aware precision routing framework on benchmark datasets, comparing it with state-of-the-art precision routing methods and performing ablation studies to quantify the impact of spectral quantization theory and geometric subspace diagnostics. 

