    "Short Hypothesis": "Spectral curvature-aware precision routing can improve the accuracy and efficiency of machine learning models by adaptively allocating precision and optimizing geometric subspace diagnostics.",
    "Related Work": "Existing works on precision routing and geometric subspace diagnostics have shown promising results, but they often rely on heuristic approaches. Our proposal introduces a spectral curvature-aware precision routing framework that integrates spectral quantization theory with geometric subspace diagnostics.",
    "Abstract": "This proposal introduces a novel spectral curvature-aware precision routing framework for machine learning. Our approach adapts precision and optimizes routing protocols using spectral quantization theory and geometric subspace diagnostics, improving model accuracy and efficiency.",
