    "Title": "Curvature-Aware Precision Routing for Machine Learning Optimization",
    "Short Hypothesis": "Curvature-aware precision routing frameworks can improve the efficiency and accuracy of machine learning models by adaptively adjusting the precision of model weights and activations during training.",
    "Related Work": "Recent works have explored the use of precision routing frameworks for machine learning optimization, but few have considered the impact of curvature on the routing process. This proposal builds on existing work in this area and introduces a novel curvature-aware approach.",
    "Abstract": "This proposal introduces a curvature-aware precision routing framework for machine learning optimization. The framework adaptively adjusts the precision of model weights and activations during training based on the curvature of the loss landscape. We demonstrate the effectiveness of our approach on a range of benchmark datasets and show that it can improve the efficiency and accuracy of machine learning models.",
    "Experiments": [
        "Experiment 1: Evaluate the effectiveness of the curvature-aware precision routing framework on a range of benchmark datasets.",
        "Experiment 2: Compare the performance of the curvature-aware precision routing framework with existing precision routing frameworks.",
        "Experiment 3: Investigate the impact of curvature on the routing process and the resulting model accuracy."
    ],
    "Risk Factors and Limitations": [
        "The curvature-aware precision routing framework may require additional computational resources to compute the curvature of the loss landscape.",
        "The framework may not be effective for all types of machine learning models or datasets."
    ]
}} 

