    "Title": "Hardware-Aware Sparse Neural Network Kernels for Commodity GPUs",
    "Short Hypothesis": "By optimizing CUDA kernels for sparse neural networks and leveraging hardware-aware heuristics, we can achieve significant speedups on commodity GPUs without sacrificing accuracy.",
    "Related Work": "Existing work on sparse neural networks has focused on theoretical guarantees and software-level optimizations. In contrast, our proposal focuses on hardware-aware kernel optimizations, which have been shown to be crucial for achieving high performance on commodity GPUs. Our work builds upon existing research on optimized CUDA kernels, but extends it to the specific context of sparse neural networks.",
    "Abstract": "We propose a novel approach to optimizing sparse neural networks on commodity GPUs. By leveraging hardware-aware heuristics and optimizing CUDA kernels, we can achieve significant speedups without sacrificing accuracy. Our approach focuses on kernel-level throughput engineering, memory-bandwidth utilization, and tensor-core occupancy, and is evaluated using reproducible benchmarks and nvprof/Nsight traces. We demonstrate the effectiveness of our approach on a range of sparse neural network architectures and datasets, and show that it can be used to achieve state-of-the-art performance on commodity GPUs.",
    "Experiments": "We will conduct a range of experiments to evaluate the effectiveness of our approach, including: (1) optimizing CUDA kernels for sparse neural networks using hardware-aware heuristics, (2) evaluating the performance of our optimized kernels on a range of sparse neural network architectures and datasets, and (3) comparing our approach to existing software-level optimizations. We will use reproducible benchmarks and nvprof/Nsight traces to evaluate performance, and will report results in terms of wall-clock latency, tokens-per-second, and energy per token.",
    "Risk Factors and Limitations": "The main risk factor for this proposal is that our optimized kernels may not generalize to all sparse neural network architectures and datasets. To mitigate this risk, we will evaluate our approach on a range of architectures and datasets, and will use hardware-aware heuristics to optimize our kernels. Another limitation of our approach is that it requires access to commodity GPUs and specialized hardware, which may not be available to all researchers. To address this limitation, we will make our optimized kernels and evaluation code publicly available, and will provide detailed instructions for reproducing our results."
  }
}
