tization, and evaluate the tradeoff between compression ratio and model performance. Specifically, we will use the following evaluation metrics: (1) compression ratio, (2) model accuracy, and (3) rate-distortion curve. We will also analyze the computational complexity of our approach and compare it to existing methods.', 'Risk Factors and Limitations': 'One potential risk factor is that our approach may not be directly applicable to all types of neural networks or compression scenarios. Additionally, the development of efficient algorithms for computing the rate-distortion function may be challenging. However, we believe that our approach has the potential to provide significant improvements in compression efficiency, and that the benefits outweigh the risks.'}
