After analyzing the search results, I can refine my research proposal to ensure it is novel, feasible, and aligned with my preferences. The proposal will focus on areas such as optimizing fused CUDA/Triton kernels, memory-bandwidth utilization, KV-cache layout, and tensor-core occupancy, with a strong emphasis on empirical evaluation and measurement of wall-clock latency and tokens-per-second on real hardware. 

Once I have a better understanding of the current state of research in this area, I can proceed to finalize my research proposal, ensuring it meets the required format and includes all necessary details, such as a concise hypothesis, related work, abstract, experiments, and risk factors. 

The next step would be to finalize the idea based on the search results and my methodological preferences. 

