ARGUMENTS:
{"idea": {
    "Name": "gpu_kernel_optimization",
    "Title": "Optimizing Machine Learning Model Inference on Commodity GPUs with Kernel-Level Throughput Engineering",
    "Short Hypothesis": "By applying kernel-level throughput engineering and hardware-faithful evaluation, we can achieve significant improvements in machine learning model inference speed on commodity GPUs, leading to faster and more efficient deployment of AI models in real-world applications.",
    "Related Work": "Recent research has focused on optimizing machine learning model inference using various techniques such as quantization, sparsity, and layer-skipping. However, these approaches often rely on theoretical bounds or simulations, rather than empirical measurements on real hardware. Our proposal builds upon existing work by emphasizing the importance of hardware-faithful evaluation and kernel-level optimization, as seen in studies such as AMP-ViT, SNIP, and EMQ.",
    "Abstract": "This research proposal aims to optimize machine learning model inference on commodity GPUs using kernel-level throughput engineering and hardware-faithful evaluation. By applying techniques such as fused CUDA/Triton kernel optimization, memory-bandwidth utilization, KV-cache layout, and tensor-core occupancy, we can achieve significant improvements in inference speed. Our approach emphasizes empirical evaluation and measurement of wall-clock latency and tokens-per-second on real hardware, ensuring that our results are reproducible and relevant to real-world applications.",
    "Experiments": "We will conduct a series of experiments to evaluate the effectiveness of our optimization techniques, including: (1) optimizing fused CUDA/Triton kernels for popular machine learning models, (2) measuring the impact of memory-bandwidth utilization and KV-cache layout on inference speed, and (3) evaluating the benefits of tensor-core occupancy on commodity GPUs. We will use a combination of profiling tools, such as nvprof and Nsight, to collect detailed measurements of kernel performance, memory bandwidth, and tensor-core utilization.",
    "Risk Factors and Limitations": "The main risk factors and limitations of our proposal include: (1) the complexity of optimizing kernel-level throughput engineering, which may require significant expertise and resources, (2) the potential for limited improvements in inference speed due to hardware constraints, and (3) the need for careful evaluation and measurement to ensure that our results are reproducible and relevant to real-world applications."
}}
