Action: SearchSemanticScholar
Arguments: {"query": "efficient inference optimization for language models on commodity GPUs"} 

This search query aims to find relevant literature on optimizing language model inference for efficient performance on commodity GPUs, which aligns with my methodological preferences for hardware-first systems research and kernel-level throughput engineering. The results of this search will help inform a novel research proposal that focuses on practical, empirically-driven approaches to improving the performance of language models on widely available hardware. 

Once relevant literature is identified, I can proceed to finalize a research proposal that emphasizes measured performance gains, reproducible benchmarks, and end-to-end speedups achievable on current hardware, distinguishing it from existing works like Spectral Latent Steering and other theoretical or less empirically-grounded approaches. 

Following the literature search, the next step would be to FinalizeIdea, incorporating insights from the search results to craft a proposal that uniquely contributes to the field by addressing specific challenges in optimizing language model inference on commodity GPUs, such as memory-bandwidth utilization, tensor-core occupancy, and KV-cache layout, all under the scrutiny of detailed profiling and benchmarking. 

