This search query aims to find relevant papers and research on optimizing CUDA kernels for low-latency language models, which aligns with my methodological preferences as a hardware-first systems researcher. The goal is to identify potential areas for improvement and explore new ideas for optimizing kernel-level throughput engineering for efficient inference. 

After conducting this search, I plan to propose a novel machine learning research idea that focuses on areas aligned with my preferences, such as kernel-level optimization, memory-bandwidth utilization, and tensor-core occupancy, with a focus on achieving measurable wall-clock latency improvements on real hardware. 

